SIMPLE: water_tower
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Water tower
<hw>Wa"ter tow"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>A large metal pipe
made to be extended vertically by sections, and used for discharging
water upon burning buildings.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tower or standpipe used as a water storage
reservoir, to deliver water at a required head of pressure, as to a
fountain.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water tree</ent>⟦br⟧
